INSERT INTO `pages` VALUES (641, 'DotNodeHelpFaq', '2005-01-15 11:21:31', '=====History=====\n ===What does .node mean?===\n It''s a combination of Dot and Node\n The dot, often used on the Internet with domain names, is used as a starting point, like communities. The node shows routes and crosses between all the points, like similarities between all communities.\n The combination of these two words is a good idea of what .node can do for you.\n\n ===Launch of .node===\n .node''s basic development began on April, 30th 2004.\n \n=====Advantages=====\n ===I''m currently registered on another Social Network. What''s the benefit of me using .node?===\n It''s in your language! .node in naturally multilingual and if your language does not appear, don''t hesitate to go to the [[/communities/view/3 .node - dev community]] and volunteer to be a translator. With .node you''ve got a homepage, which you can access like http://your_id.dotnode.com . Also, functionalities like online sharing of objects or group buying are planed on .node in the future.\n\n ===I''ve got a lot of ideas! May I tell you?===\n With a lot of pleasure! .node is YOUR Social Network and we welcome good ideas. Please subscribe to [[/communities/view/3 .node - dev community]] and [[/communities/view/241 write your ideas]].\n\n\n=====Authentification/ ID / Password=====\n ===Why must my ID/Password must be secret?===\n Because they are your key on .node. A badly intentioned person can steal your information, or usurp your ID on communities, discredit yourself or use .node illegally if you aren''t careful. This is the reason why passwords must be change regularly.\n\n ===Forgotten ID / Password===\n On the connection page, there is a link to email you the steps to change your password or remind you your ID. Click on this link to go directly: [[/error/forgot_password]]\n\n ===Can I unsubscribe?===\n At anytime you can unscribe from .node service by [[/messages/write/00112233445566778899001122334455/contact sending a message to the moderator]].\n\n ===What about the unsubscription of the friend who invited me? Do I have to leave too?===\n No! Only the link between you and the rest of .node network is broken. You do not have to unsubscribe too.  You need to find a friend to make a new link. ;)\n\n\n=====Basic functionalities=====\n ===Why can''t I join .node?===\n .node works on the trusted network principal. It''s the reason that you must receive a .node member''s email invitation to join.\n\n ===What about all these questions to complete my profile?===\n It''s simply to have more interesting exchanges with other members. Don''t waste your time talking with people who do not agree with your ideas or hobbies. If you honnestly complete your profile, you reduce this factor and increase your chance to meet interresting people!\n\n ===Okay, but what about my privacy?===\n .node Team respects your privacy and will not sell or give away your information. It is kept private (this is the same way for your email, ID and password). You can adjust what information other members can see by specifying your relationship to your friends (You / Friends / Friends of Friends / All members / Everyone).\n\n ===Utility of writing links?===\n In order to share the maximum amount of interesting information, you should consider sharing your bookmarks. You''ll have a backup if you change your browser or if your computer crashes but even more important, you could share your links with all .node members. Who knows? You could find an interesting link on someone''s profile.  ;)\n\n ===Do you say "Blog"?===\n A Blog or WeBlog is a little space who you can write all you want to say. You can use it like a newspaper, list tips, write a journal, or even list recipes. All entries are sorted in reverse chronological order (newest first), to easily view news.\n\n ===What about communities?===\n Communities are places based on one particular topic. They works like forums, everybody can write a short message at the end of the feed. Communities could manage events or organize meetings with community members for example.\n\n ===Could I delete a community?===\n You must be the admin and alone in a community to delete it.\n\n ===What can I do with the Messages?===\n It''s like your favorite mailbox, but only for .node use. You can send and receive .node messages to other members in a more private way than communities.\n\n ===Is there a limit to my account?===\n No, you can create as many communities as you want, and get an unlimited number of friends. There isn''t limit on the message either.  ;)', '', 'de_DE', 'AleXx', 'AleXx', 'Y', 'page', '');
